# Monitoring Design

## Purpose

Monitoring is included early in the Charlotte_2026 architecture so infrastructure and application health can be validated before adding more complex stateful services such as RDS.

## Monitoring Stack

The current monitoring stack includes:

- Prometheus
- Grafana
- Node Exporter

## Prometheus

Prometheus collects metrics from configured scrape targets.

Current targets:

- Prometheus itself on port 9090
- Node Exporter on port 9100

## Node Exporter

Node Exporter exposes Linux host metrics, including:

- CPU
- Memory
- Disk
- Filesystem
- Network

## Grafana

Grafana provides dashboard visualization for Prometheus metrics.

## Current Access Model

The monitoring server is deployed in a private subnet. Direct browser access is not expected.

The intended access pattern is:

```text
Browser
   |
   v
Public NGINX Server
   |
   v
Private Monitoring Server
   |
   |-- Grafana :3000
   |-- Prometheus :9090